  "Different countries' economic cycles are not perfectly correlated, so international stocks may rise when domestic stocks fall": "",
  "Foreign stocks always outperform domestic stocks, as conventional diversification theory would suggest": "",
  "It is required by US law, which represents a common but incomplete view of how these diversification dynamics": "",
  "International diversification reduces portfolio risk because economic conditions differ across countries. When one market struggles, others may thrive, smoothing overall portfolio returns.": "",
